Can You Chip In?



The Internet Archive is growing faster than ever before, and we need your help. As an independent nonprofit, we build and maintain all our own systems, but we don’t charge for access, sell user information, or run ads—instead we're powered by donations averaging $30. Unfortunately, fewer than 1 in 1000 of our patrons donate.



We don't ask often, but right now, we have a 2-to-1 Matching Gift Campaign, tripling the impact of every donation. If you find all these bits and bytes useful, please pitch in.



—Brewster Kahle, Founder, Internet Archive
